docs.abstract: Prosecutors claim Representative Duncan Hunter and his wife spent over $250,000 of campaign funds on personal items. Here is an explanation of the indictment filed on Tuesday.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors claim Representative Duncan Hunter and his wife spent over $250,000 of campaign funds on personal items. Here is an explanation of the indictment filed on Tuesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Representative Duncan Hunter, Republican of California, and his wife, Margaret Hunter, were indicted on Tuesday, accused of spending more than $250,000 in campaign funds on personal expenses — including a vacation to Italy, family dental bills and plane tickets for a pet — and then lying to the Federal Election Commission.

headline.main: The Indictment of Duncan Hunter, Explained

docs.abstract: Do you remember Pizzagate? It’s a little like that: a web of baseless conspiracy theories. And its supporters were highly visible at an event for the president in Florida.
docs.snippet: Do you remember Pizzagate? It’s a little like that: a web of baseless conspiracy theories. And its supporters were highly visible at an event for the president in Florida.
docs.lead_paragraph: Those watching President Trump’s rally in Tampa on Tuesday couldn’t help but be exposed to a fringe movement that discusses several loosely connected and vaguely defined — and baseless — conspiracy theories.

headline.main: What Is QAnon: Explaining the Internet Conspiracy Theory That Showed Up at a Trump Rally

docs.abstract: The top three Democratic candidates are 78, 76 and 70 years old and one of them, Bernie Sanders, went to the hospital with chest pain. Voters want experienced leaders, but exactly how much life experience do they want?
docs.snippet: The top three Democratic candidates are 78, 76 and 70 years old and one of them, Bernie Sanders, went to the hospital with chest pain. Voters want experienced leaders, but exactly how much life experience do they want?
docs.lead_paragraph: For months, Senator Bernie Sanders brushed off questions about his age, offering a simple, six-word mantra to those who doubt he’s energetic enough to run for president: “Follow me around the campaign trail.”

headline.main: Is Age Only a Number, Even When You’re Running for President?
headline.print_headline: Age May Be Just a Number, but Will Chest Pains Give Voters Pause?

docs.lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has raised $15.2 million in the past three months, his campaign said Thursday, a drop-off of $7 million from the previous quarter and a sum that falls short of two leading Democratic rivals.

headline.main: Biden Fund-Raising Effort Trails Sanders and Buttigieg
headline.print_headline: Biden Slips Behind Rivals, With $15 Million in Quarter

docs.abstract: The Midwest mayor is making an appeal to rural voters and hoping a massive ground game delivers a top-tier caucus finish.
docs.snippet: The Midwest mayor is making an appeal to rural voters and hoping a massive ground game delivers a top-tier caucus finish.
docs.lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — On the day House Democrats opened an impeachment inquiry of President Trump last week, Pete Buttigieg was being grilled by Iowa voters on other subjects: how to loosen the grip of the rich on government, how to restore science to policymaking, how to reduce child poverty.

headline.main: Flush With Cash, Pete Buttigieg Bets His Campaign on a Breakthrough in Iowa
headline.print_headline: Buttigieg, Flush With Cash, Bets Campaign on a Breakthrough in Iowa

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The campaign trail can bring fraught encounters for a presidential candidate. At a televised forum on L.G.B.T.Q. issues on Thursday, Senator Elizabeth Warren was asked to consider a hypothetical one.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Has Quick Comeback to Gay Marriage Question
